I met Fredy for the first time in Vienna during a ceremony about seven years ago. When I heard him sing for the first time, he came across like a seraph, a mythical, winged ambassador from another dimension, gifted with a voice that seemed designed to shake temples. 

Later, I realized Fredy was not just a shaman or a seraph, but also a great musician and a very enjoyable gentleman with whom it is impossible to spend time without laughing.

Check out the video in full 4K resolution on YouTube @ https://t.co/xJmS4ZuHpX

All Together (Todos Juntos) - A Song of a Colombian Shaman

Fredy Velasquez is a shamanistic musician from the Inkal Awá territory in southwest Colombia, near the Ecuadorian border. Fredy's music reflects his community's rich cultural heritage and personal life journey.

From a young age, Fredy showed a natural talent for music, nurtured through his empirical training and involvement in various folklore groups across Colombia. His voice has led many musical projects, including collaborations with the Putumayo Group. Fredy's artistic path has taken him from his homeland to South and Central America, the USA, and now Europe.

In his song "All Together (Todos Juntos)," Fredy captures the sounds of rivers, jungles, and mountains, blending traditional Colombian music with diverse European influences. 

Fredy's lyrics revolve around the question, "Why do we separate each other if the Earth wants us to connect?"

Produced by Jelena Garcia Gvozdecka, Fredy's partner in organizing shamanistic retreats worldwide.
